The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | DDCA panel resigns
                                                                                                                       7                                      DDCA panel resigns
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) on Sunday disbanded its grounds and pitches committee with immediate effect following the abandonment of the fifth and final India-Sri Lanka ODI at the Kotla.         
	Several hours later, in a related development, all members of the grounds and pitches committee of the Delhi and Districts Cricket Association (DDCA)  chairman Chetan Chauhan, convenor Sunil Dev and curator Vijay Bahadur Mishra  resigned owning moral responsibility for the pitch fiasco.         
	At a meeting of senior officials of the DDCA, the chairman and members of the grounds and pitches committee of the DDCA, including the curator, resigned owing moral responsibility after the abandonment of the India-Sri Lanka ODI, DDCA secretary S. P. Bansal said in a statement.         
	Earlier, a statement issued by BCCI secretary N. Srinivasan said: The BCCI has disbanded its grounds and pitches committee with immediate effect,         
	The decision to disband the five-member BCCI committee, headed by Daljit Singh, came hours after the final one-dayer was called off because of a dangerous pitch.         
	Apart from Daljit, other members of the panel are Dhiraj Parsana (west), PR Viswanathan (south), Rajiv Gokhale (central) and Ratul Das (east).         
	The game was abandoned after Sri Lanka captain Kumar Sangakkara refused to play on a dangerous pitch.         
	The visitors were tottering at 83 for five when Thilina Kandamby complained to the on-field umpires about the condition of the pitch.                                                                                                                     
